== Overview ==
The '''Talsian Warfront''' (commonly referred to as '''Talsia''' or '''Tals''') is the second major outland zone available to [[Controller|Controllers]], accessible after establishing a foothold in [[Vulcore Plain|Vulcore]]. It is an active military theatre — a vast, contested warzone where [[CyCorps]] forces and their allied [[Legionnaires]] are locked in an ongoing conflict against the '''Federate''' military. Unlike Vulcore's open wasteland, Talsia is a structured battlefield with defined sectors, fortified positions, warships, armoured columns, and elite enemy units.

Talsia is the primary source of '''Talsian Rank Points (TRP)''', '''Accolades''', and '''Mission Reward Points (MRP)''', which together drive the progression system for mid-to-late game Controllers. The zone is divided into two main sectors — '''Delta''' and '''Alpha''' — plus the '''Ruins''' area, each with escalating difficulty and rewards.

