Talsia is entered from the [[Workshop]] once the Controller meets the prerequisites. Upon entering, the Controller chooses between '''Delta Sector''' and '''Alpha Sector''' as their starting camp. Alpha Sector becomes accessible at '''750 TRP'''.

== Theme ==
The Talsian Warfront is a war-torn military environment defined by:
* Active combat between CyCorps/Legionnaire forces and the Federate military
* Armoured columns, infantry platoons, bunkers, fire bases, and fortified walls
* Federate warships — Destroyers, Cruisers, and Battle Cruisers — patrolling the skies
* Elite '''True Guard''' units defending key installations and ambushing CyCarriers
* Talsian dust storms that sweep across the battlefield
* Ruined cities (notably the remnants of '''Neoforina''') and contested valleys
* Tactical Re-Arming Facilities (TRAFs) — Federate fortresses that are among the hardest encounters in the zone
* Super Tanks — massive Federate armoured units that roam the warfront

The atmosphere is one of constant attrition. Controllers must manage their [[KCharge]] carefully — many encounters can be skipped to conserve KC, and not every battle yields TRP or MRP.

== Sectors / Sub-Zones ==

=== Delta Sector ===
The entry-level sector of the Talsian Warfront. Delta is the first area Controllers operate in and contains lighter Federate forces compared to Alpha. It is the primary grinding zone for Controllers building up their TRP from 0 to approximately 750–800.

'''Key features:'''
* Standard Federate infantry patrols, tank squads, bunkers, and fire bases
* Mission outpost offering Delta-specific missions (see [[#Missions|Missions]])
* Federate Drop Crates — supply crates dropped from aircraft; can be investigated for [[Mission Reward Points]] or set as ambushes
* Federate Communications Relay Stations — can be destroyed or scanned for rewards
* Valleys — optional terrain that can be entered; contain enemies and loot but are not required
* Ruined City ('''Neoforina''') — the remnants of a destroyed city; can be explored
* Bunkers — Federate fortified positions; attacking them yields [[Accolades]] (3 per bunker)
* Fire Bases — heavily defended Federate launch sites; optional encounters
* Uncrewed Tanks — abandoned Federate tanks that can be hijacked using a [[Comwave Scanner]] via an [[Overseer]]
* Federate Armour Spotted — random tank encounters; can be attacked or avoided
* Surrendering Troops — captured Federate soldiers; can be handed over, killed, or freed
* Survivors — found after battles; can be taken to camp, marked, or left

'''Encounters that give TRP/MRP:'''
Missions are the primary source of TRP and MRP. In Delta, the following give TRP/MRP:
* All mission completions (Sector Patrol, Disrupt Bombing Runs, Tank Threat, Freighter Escort, Priority Defence)
* Bunkers (3 Accolades each)
* Tank squads (when encountered as mission objectives)
* Destroyers (25 Rank Points + 15 Accolades on kill)

=== Alpha Sector ===
The advanced sector of the Talsian Warfront, accessible at '''750 TRP'''. Alpha contains significantly harder Federate forces, including heavy tank formations, elite infantry, and warships. It is the primary grinding zone from ~750 TRP onward.

'''Key features:'''
* Heavy Federate armour: Main Battle Tanks, Heavy Siege Tanks, [[Ae7 Barrier Tank|Ae7 Barrier Tanks]], [[C6II Enertron|C6II Enertrons]], Amplifier Tanks, Syncron Tanks, Director Tanks, Concussion Tanks
* Federate infantry: Heavy Infantry, Siege Blaster Squads, Grenadiers, Lieutenants, Heavy Shield Projectors, Bombardiers
* Warships: Destroyers, Cruisers, and Battle Cruisers
* TRAFs (Tactical Re-Arming Facilities) — see [[#TRAF|TRAF section]]
* Super Tanks — [[Hulkram]], [[Moriartium]], [[Damostator]] (see [[#Super Tanks|Super Tanks]])
* Carrier SOS events — [[CyCarrier]] ambushed by [[True Guard]]; can be aided for rewards
* Crash Troopers — elite Federate jetpack infantry; appear during Blockade missions and Carrier SOS
* Storm Troopers — fast APC-transported infantry; appear during Besieged Base missions
* Battle Wreckage — aftermath of battles; can be investigated for components/MRP
* Federate Response Teams — sent after the squad when operating in the area
* Rogue Cybots — rogue bot squads encountered in Alpha

'''Encounters that give TRP/MRP:'''
* All mission completions (Reinforce Besieged Base, Chassis Recovery, Mining Facility Raid, Free Patrol, Destroy Cruiser, Blockade)
* Destroyers (25 Rank Points + 15 Accolades)
* Cruisers (100 Rank Points + 15 Accolades — best TRP-per-mission in the game until 18k TRP)
* Battle Cruisers (75 Rank Points)
* TRAFs (75 Rank Points on completion)
* Carrier SOS (15 Accolades + experience)
* Bunkers (3 Accolades each)
* Communications Relay Stations (15 MRP)
* Crash Troopers (15 Accolades)
* Federate Jet (10 Accolades + 5000 XP)
* Super Tanks (variable rewards — see [[#Super Tanks|Super Tanks]])

'''Encounters that do NOT give TRP/MRP (can be skipped to save KC):'''
* Standard infantry patrols (no Accolades unless mission-specific)
* Free Patrol mission — not recommended; poor TRP/MRP ratio
* Most random patrol encounters outside of mission objectives
* Valleys (optional)

=== Ruins (Neoforina) ===
The remnants of the city of '''Neoforina''', accessible from the main patrol area. The Ruins are an optional exploration area.

'''Key features:'''
* Can be entered when the squad's course brings them near the ruins
* Contains Federate forces, potential loot, and unique encounters
* '''Storage Bunkers''' — can be opened using a [[Security Countermand]] module for rewards
* '''Command Centers''' — Federate headquarters with database access; using a [[Comwave Scanner]] grants intelligence bonuses
* '''Super Credit Cache''' — a Federate mercenary payment cache worth $500,000; requires a Comwave Scanner to access
* '''Experience Bonus''' — Comwave Scanner can discover Federate tactical data, granting a x2 experience bonus
* '''Trap Discovered''' — bases may be booby-trapped; an [[Anomaly Detector]] can detect and avoid the trap, rewarding the full base contents
* '''Perimeter Defences''' — multi-stage base assault with walls, turrets, and interior defenders

