== Talsian Rank Points (TRP) ==

'''Talsian Rank Points (TRP)''' are the primary progression metric in Talsia. They are earned from:
* Mission completions (primary source)
* Destroying Destroyers (+25 TRP)
* Destroying Cruisers (+100 TRP)
* Completing TRAFs (+75 TRP)
* Battle Cruiser victories (+75 TRP)

TRP determines the Controller's '''Talsian Rank''' and unlocks awards, new chassis, and increased rewards.

=== TRP Cap at 18,000 ===
At '''18,000 TRP''', the experience and credits earned per MRP conversion reach their maximum value (~7,500 XP per MRP at max BM). Beyond 18,000 TRP, additional TRP no longer increases the MRP conversion rate. This means:
* Controllers at 18k+ TRP can abort unwanted missions (costs −50 TRP and Accolades) without significant penalty
* Mining Facility Raid and Blockade become the best missions (highest MRP yield)
* Chassis Recovery and Reinforce Besieged Base can be aborted (recover + abort) — no need to exit and re-enter patrol
* All patrol encounters can be attacked freely (1–2 KC each at high BM)
* TRAFs are no longer necessary for TRP farming

=== Raven Chassis Unlock at 18,000 TRP ===
<gallery widths="160" heights="120">
File:Raven.png|[[Raven]] — advanced chassis unlocked at high TRP
</gallery>
Upon reaching '''18,000 TRP''', the new '''Raven''' chassis is unlocked. This is a significant milestone reward for Controllers who have invested heavily in Talsia progression.

== Mission Reward Points (MRP) ==

'''Mission Reward Points (MRP)''' are accumulated during patrol from:
* Battle victories (variable MRP per battle)
* Bunker destructions (5 MRP per bunker)
* Communications Relay destructions (15 MRP)
* Federate Drop Crate investigations (4 MRP for destroying supplies)
* Chassis recoveries (5 Accolades per chassis + MRP)
* Various other encounters

At mission completion, all accumulated MRP are converted into experience and credits. The formula scales with:
* '''TRP''' — higher TRP = more XP per MRP (caps at 18,000 TRP)
* '''BM (Battle Merit)''' — higher BM = more XP per MRP (caps at ~14M BM)

At maximum TRP (18k) and high BM (~30M), a single mission can yield 1–2 million XP and $1–2M credits from MRP conversion alone.

== Accolades ==

'''Accolades''' are the secondary currency of Talsia, earned from:
* Mission completions (variable per mission type)
* Bunker destructions (3 Accolades per bunker)
* Crash Trooper defeats (15 Accolades)
* Destroyer kills (15 Accolades)
* Federate Jet kills (10 Accolades)
* Carrier SOS victories (15 Accolades)
* Various patrol encounters

Accolades are spent on:
* Hiring mercenaries (see [[#Mercenary Outpost|Mercenary Outpost]])
* Purchasing Technology segments (Plasma Tech, Storm Weapons Tech — 2,250 each)
* Purchasing Obliterators (1,000 each)
* Purchasing super weapons (see [[#Accolade Shop|Accolade Shop]])

