== TRAF (Tactical Re-Arming Facility) ==

A '''TRAF''' (Tactical Re-Arming Facility) is a heavily fortified Federate installation found in Talsia. TRAFs are multi-round encounters — the hardest repeatable challenge in the zone — and reward '''75 Talsian Rank Points''' upon completion.

TRAFs are discovered via an '''Incoming Transmission''' event ordering their destruction, or by stumbling upon them during patrol ('''TRAF Located''' event).

=== TRAF Structure ===
TRAFs consist of 4 rounds of escalating difficulty:

'''Round 1 — Outer Turrets:'''
* Typically: 1–3 Uplink Towers, 2–4 PR600 Turrets, 3–6 other turrets (exact count depends on BM)
* Uplink Commands project 9,000 shield each with heavy armour and shield deflection
* Rhinos deal ~5,000 damage (15,000 with crits — uncommon)
* FGSI Turrets deal shield damage and drain; they stop operating when Uplink Commands are destroyed
* '''Strategy note:''' Drain both Uplink Commands first, then kill them. FGSI Turrets become inactive after Uplink Commands are destroyed.

'''Round 2 — Wall Turrets / Forward Wall:'''
* Typically: 1 Reinforced Wall, 2–3 Rhinos, 1–3 Uplink Towers, 1–2 SR180 Receptors
* The '''Reinforced Wall''' provides drain deflection to all units behind it — SR180 turrets and Uplink Commands cannot be drained until the wall is killed (not just drained)
* SR180 Receptors are heavy drain turrets that crit frequently
* '''Critical note:''' The Reinforced Wall is very hard to kill without a high-crit [[Obliterator]] on a Crusader. The wall's deflection must be broken first.

'''Round 3 — Inner Wall:'''
* Same as Round 2 but with additional tanks
* Tanks are not significantly more dangerous than Round 2 — use the same approach

'''Round 4 — True Guard (Final Round):'''
* True Guard units, Manium Firesprays, Cortex Tanks, Storm Bringer tanks, SR180 Receptors
* True Guard and Manium Firesprays deal ~6,000 damage with crits (frequent)
* Storm Bringer tanks deal ~10,500 damage with crits (less frequent)
* Up to 3 True Guard Shielding units at high BM (10M+)
* '''Do not stop or recover before this round''' — doing so triggers another Round 3 equivalent
* Cortex Tanks are the True Guard version of Seers — they provide deflection, fire rate, and energy bonuses

'''TRAF Reward:'''
* '''75 Talsian Rank Points'''
* Chance to receive the '''Ravager''' super weapon (see [[#Ravager|Ravager]])

=== The Ravager ===
<gallery widths="160" heights="120">
File:Obliterator.jpg|[[Ravager]] — Ravager Superweapon
</gallery>
The '''[[Ravager]]''' is a rare super weapon that can drop as a reward from completing a TRAF. It is considered one of the best weapons in the game:
* '''3,000 shield damage'''
* '''1,750 armour damage'''
* '''500 energy drain'''
* Weight: 500 kg (requires 676+ weapon tech on [[Crusader]] to equip; high payload needed)
* Equipped on [[Crusader]] alongside [[Tribolt Hydron]] reactor and [[Master Fire Director|MFDs]] for maximum effect

