=== Destroyer ===
A Federate warship encountered in both Delta and Alpha Sectors. Destroyers are spotted on the horizon and can be attacked or avoided.

* '''Composition:''' Bridge + Destroyer Hull + 2x Shield Generator + 12x Heavy Gun Turret
* '''Reward:''' 25 [[Talsian Rank Points|Rank Points]] + 15 [[Accolades]]
* '''Encounter:''' "Controller, a Destroyer has been spotted on the horizon. What are our orders?"
* '''Note:''' Destroyers fire barrages before the squad can close to attack range, dealing pre-battle damage

=== Cruiser ===
A Federate Cruiser that has broken off from the main fleet. The primary target of the '''Destroy Cruiser''' mission.

* '''Composition:''' Bridge + Cruiser Hull + 6x Shield Generator + 3x Devastator Battery
* '''Reward:''' 100 [[Talsian Rank Points|Rank Points]] + 15 [[Accolades]] (mission completion)
* '''Mission:''' "A Federate Cruiser has broken off from a main fleet and is vulnerable to attack. Destroy it."
* '''Note:''' Best TRP-per-mission in the game until the 18k TRP cap. Do not change this mission when available.

=== Battle Cruiser ===
A massive Federate warship — one of the most dangerous encounters in Talsia. Battle Cruisers are spotted by long-range radar and can be avoided or engaged.

* '''Reward:''' 75 [[Talsian Rank Points|Rank Points]]
* '''Encounter:''' "Warning! Long range radar has picked up a gigantic federate warship. Although not many have been encountered, we are led to believe it may be a Battle Cruiser."
* '''Structure:''' Multi-stage encounter — long-range bombardment phase, then direct engagement
* '''Note:''' Requires significant preparation (25,200+ projected shields, high drain deflection). At endgame, all-attack the Battle Cruiser hull for a quick kill.

== Carrier SOS ==
<gallery widths="160" heights="120">
File:Cycarrier_hull.png
</gallery>
The '''Carrier SOS''' is a random event in Alpha Sector where a CyCarrier is ambushed by True Guard forces.

* '''Trigger:''' "Incoming Transmission: Carrier SOS — Emergency Transmission: [[True Guard]] ambush. [[CyCarrier]] in your vicinity requesting immediate assistance. Send help ASAP."
* '''Choices:''' AID CYCARRIER | IGNORE
* '''Reward for aiding:''' 15 [[Accolades]] + experience + potential encounter with [[General Vangould]]
* '''[[General Vangould]]:''' A named [[True Guard]] Field Marshal who commands the ambush force. His tank escapes before destruction, but the battle is still won. Defeating his forces yields additional rewards.
* '''Note:''' Carrier SOS is a good source of [[Accolades]] and experience. The [[True Guard]] forces are dangerous — ensure adequate shielding and drain deflection before engaging.

== Unique Encounters ==

=== Federate Drop Crate ===
Federate supply crates dropped from aircraft. Can be investigated for rewards.
* '''Choices:''' IGNORE CRATE | INVESTIGATE
* If investigated: DESTROY CRATE (4 MRP) | SET AMBUSH (ambush the Federates who come to collect it)
* If the crate is empty: "Looks like the Feds beat us to it Controller."
* If the crate contains a Repair Kit: can be used for one-time repairs to Federate tanks/bots

=== Uncrewed Tanks ===
Abandoned Federate tanks discovered during patrol.
* '''Choices:''' ATTEMPT HIJACK | LEAVE
* Requires a [[Comwave Scanner]] (via [[Overseer]]) to hijack
* Success: "Uplink Successful — We have hijacked a Federate tank and have linked it to your uplink channel through our [[Overseer]]."

=== Surrendering Troops ===
Remaining Federate soldiers who surrender after a base is captured.
* '''Choices:''' HAND PRISONERS OVER | KILL PRISONERS | SET PRISONERS FREE
* Handing over prisoners: 30 MRP reward from CyCorps

=== Dust Storm ===
A Talsian dust storm sweeps over the squad's position.
* Causes temporary communications loss
* May cause minor damage and energy disruption ("Light Damage")
* Passes harmlessly in most cases

=== Valley Entrance ===
An optional terrain feature — a valley with relatively undisturbed terrain.
* '''Choices:''' NO | YES
* Contains enemies and potential loot
* Not required for missions; can be skipped to save KC

=== Ruined City (Neoforina) ===
The remnants of the city of Neoforina.
* '''Choices:''' NO | YES
* Contains Federate forces, storage bunkers, command centers, and potential loot
* Storage Bunkers require a [[Security Countermand]] module to open
* Command Centers with a [[Comwave Scanner]] grant database access and intelligence bonuses

=== Battle Wreckage ===
Signs of a recent battle discovered during patrol.
* '''Choices:''' IGNORE WRECKAGE | INVESTIGATE WRECKAGE
* May contain components worth MRP, or nothing ("Most of the wreckage has been disintegrated by heavy weapons fire")

=== Airstrike ===
A Federate Goshawk ground attack aircraft targets the squad.
* Sophisticated sensors make it hard to avoid
* Defeating it rewards 10 Accolades + 5,000 experience

=== Service Squad ===
A passing CyCorps service squad inspects the squad for battle damage.
* Makes repairs and provides a temporary AI boost

=== Experience Boost ===
CyCorps transmission granting a bonus multiplier to experience earnings.

=== Super Credit Cache ===
A Federate mercenary payment cache discovered using a Comwave Scanner.
* Rewards: $500,000

